commentary: H Masakadza to Anamul Haque, 1 run, OUT Oh my, that's unfortunate. They've gone to the third umpire, and it looks out. It's a slower ball on leg stump, and he works it away towards deep midwicket. They run a second and it would have been easily completed had Tamim not dropped his bat just short of reaching the bowler's end. He jammed it into the ground, looking to ground it, and it dropped out of his grasp. He had to jump into the crease, and his feet were in the air when Masakadza picked up Taylor's throw from the deep and disturbed the bails. For good measure, he threw to the other end as well, but obviously the ball became dead once Tamim was out at the bowler's end
shortText: H Masakadza to Anamul Haque, 1 run, OUT
text: Oh my, that's unfortunate. They've gone to the third umpire, and it looks out. It's a slower ball on leg stump, and he works it away towards deep midwicket. They run a second and it would have been easily completed had Tamim not dropped his bat just short of reaching the bowler's end. He jammed it into the ground, looking to ground it, and it dropped out of his grasp. He had to jump into the crease, and his feet were in the air when Masakadza picked up Taylor's throw from the deep and disturbed the bails. For good measure, he threw to the other end as well, but obviously the ball became dead once Tamim was out at the bowler's end
